						<summary>

						<p>On the west wall of the central shrine in the Kailāsanātha temple.</p>						

						<p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 49: 1118-1119 A.D.</p>						

						<p>In this inscription only the date, year 49, is mentioned. The palaeography, the high regnal year and the name Rājasundari-chaturvēdimaṅgalam suggest that this inscription belongs to the reign of Kulōttuṅga I. </p>						

						<p>It records some injunctions regarding the eligibility of candidates for selection framed by the <hi rend="italic">Peruṅguṟi Mahāsabhā</hi> of Rājasundari-chcharuppēdimaṅgalam.</p>						

						</summary>
